## 🎨 Design & Architecture Enhancements
- Orchestrated the transition to a modern, glassmorphic dark-theme visual editor for `GraphCanvas`.
- Restructured `GraphCanvas` by extracting `EdgeItem` into an isolated component to optimize edge rendering and eliminate expensive React re-renders on the main canvas.
- Re-architected the `useShortcut` Context and Hook pattern. Resolved a critical React lifecycle issue by implementing a callback `useRef` to prevent infinite re-registrations of event listeners.

## ⚡ Interactive UX & Animation
- Designed and implemented a high-performance SVG `EdgeFlowParticles` system leveraging raw DOM manipulation (`requestAnimationFrame`) for 60fps data flow visualization.
- Built a dynamic `ParticleBurst` component to provide immediate visual feedback upon node creation.
- Implemented `EdgePulse` animations to confirm edge connections instantly.

## 🐛 Bug Fixes & Issue Resolution
- **Node ID Gap-Filling:** Refactored the strictly auto-incrementing database-style ID logic in `graphReducer.ts`. Engineered a gap-finding algorithm so deleted Node IDs (e.g., node 3) are automatically reused to maintain logical sequential numbering for the user.
- **SVG Animation Engine Quirks:** Solved a complex browser rendering bug where CSS `transform: scale()` caused particles to collapse toward the SVG bounds instead of the node center. Rewrote the burst logic to rely purely on absolute pixel translation (`dx/dy`) and opacity.
- **Vite HMR Crashing:** Resolved a critical Vite Fast Refresh error that was killing the dev server by properly decoupling hook exports (`useShortcut.ts`) from React Context providers.
- **Animation Desync:** Fixed an issue where edge particles decoupled from the path when nodes were dragged. Moved the `getTotalLength()` calculation inside the animation loop to ensure perfect real-time arc tracking.
- **Shortcut Safety:** Patched the global shortcut listener to explicitly ignore keypresses inside `<input>` and `<textarea>` elements, preventing users from accidentally deleting edges while editing weights.

